name: Fresno
absentee_method: Merged into voters' home precincts and released with cumulative results
nyt_race_description_race: Don’t expect to see David Valadao invoking the president as he wages a tough, personal campaign to win back the Central Valley House seat he narrowly lost in 2018 to T.J. Cox, the Democratic candidate. Instead, Mr. Valadao has been portraying himself as a moderate Republican who can bridge partisan divides, while Mr. Cox has countered with a campaign tying his challenger to President Trump.
poll_display_race: Polls close at 11 p.m. Eastern time.
expectations_text_race: All active registered voters were sent mail ballots, and late-arriving mail ballots and provisional ballots will be counted in the days and weeks after the election.
expectations_text_short_race: All active registered voters were sent mail ballots, and late-arriving mail ballots and provisional ballots will be counted in the days and weeks after the election.
